  "server": {
    "name": "io.nyc.oti",
    "title": "NYC Office of Technology & Innovation (OTI)",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Agent-native access to the citywide platform the NYC Office of Technology & Innovation operates \u2014 search and register NYC Open Data datasets, discover services on the api.nyc.gov gateway and request keys, geocode addresses via GeoClient/GeoSearch, and query LinkNYC kiosks, municipal-broadband assets, public Wi-Fi hotspots, and 311 service requests.",
    "instructions": "OTI is the city's platform operator, so this server is the natural front door to the whole corpus. Use search_datasets / get_dataset to discover any of the 2,300+ NYC Open Data assets in the catalog OTI runs, and register_dataset to submit a new one (write \u2014 confirm agency, name, and description first). Use list_gateway_services / get_gateway_service to see what is published on api.nyc.gov (GeoClient, GeoSearch, ...) and request_api_key to obtain a subscription key (write \u2014 collect applicant email and use case, api.nyc.gov returns 401 until a key is granted). geocode resolves a NYC address to coordinates and the geography spine (BBL/BIN/borough/council district). find_linknyc_kiosks covers kiosk locations and live Wi-Fi/tablet/phone status; find_broadband_assets covers fiber/wireless readiness in target neighborhoods; find_wifi_hotspots covers the public Wi-Fi inventory; find_service_requests queries the 311 pipeline (the single most-viewed dataset in the city). The two write tools mutate state and require an authenticated caller."
  },
